      "content": "The \"criminal\" Latino trope often manifests as the gang member or the cartel enforcer, where their entire existence is defined by violence and illegality, regardless of the plot's actual focus. Conversely, the \"passionate\" archetype is frequently reduced to the overly dramatic lover or the volatile family patriarch whose emotional outbursts are treated as inherently exotic or untamed. These roles often lack depth, existing purely to provide immediate, easily digestible conflict or heightened melodrama for the white audience.",
